title: Unable to compile hello_world.rs to wasm
body:
Following the tutorial [here](https://hackernoon.com/compiling-rust-to-webassembly-guide-411066a69fde) I've installed Rust and Emscripten.  But when I try to compile a simple rust file to WebAssembly I get an error from llvm-ar.  I'm a total noob to Rust, enthused by the idea of a web language that doesn't suck, so apologies if I've missed something obvious.  I'm on macOS Sierra 10.12.5:
